SIMPLE: inundation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inundation
<hw>In`un*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inundatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inondation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inundating, or the state of being
inundated; an overflow; a flood; a rising and spreading of water over
grounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>inundation</qex> wide the deluge reigns,⟦br⟧
Drowns the deep valleys, and o'erspreads the plains.</q>
<rj><qau>Wilkie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An overspreading of any kind; overflowing or
superfluous abundance; a flood; a great influx; <as>as, an
<ex>inundation</ex> of tourists</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To stop the <qex>inundation</qex> of her tears.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inunderstanding</ent>⟦br⟧
